@startuml Colour Blind Mode - Sequence Diagram

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #444444
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam noteBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7

title Deuteranopia colour blind mode - toggle sequence

participant "User\n(Cmd+Shift+C)" as User
participant "ActionManager\nToggleColourBlindAction" as AM
participant "ColorThemeManager\n(static)" as CTM
participant "SettingsManager\n(singleton)" as SM
participant "ConsoleWindow\n(via WindowManager)" as CW

== Toggle ON ==

User -> AM : actionPerformed()
activate AM

AM -> CTM : isDeuteranopiaEnabled()
activate CTM
CTM --> AM : false
deactivate CTM

AM -> CTM : setDeuteranopiaMode(true)
activate CTM
note right of CTM
  deuteranopiaEnabled = true
  Static field - no I/O, instant.
end note
deactivate CTM

AM -> SM : setSetting("DEUTERANOPIA_MODE", "true")
activate SM
SM --> AM : ok
deactivate SM

AM -> CW : repaint / reapply colours
activate CW
note right of CW
  ConsoleWindow queries
  ColorThemeManager.getErrorColor()
  ColorThemeManager.getPromptColor()
  on next render.
  Returns #E69F00 (amber) for errors,
  #0072B2 (blue) for prompts.
end note
CW --> AM : done
deactivate CW
deactivate AM

== Console renders with new colours ==

CW -> CTM : getErrorColor()
activate CTM
CTM --> CW : new Color(230, 159, 0)  [#E69F00]
deactivate CTM

CW -> CTM : getPromptColor()
activate CTM
CTM --> CW : new Color(0, 114, 178)  [#0072B2]
deactivate CTM

== Toggle OFF ==

User -> AM : actionPerformed() (second press)
activate AM

AM -> CTM : isDeuteranopiaEnabled()
activate CTM
CTM --> AM : true
deactivate CTM

AM -> CTM : setDeuteranopiaMode(false)
activate CTM
note right of CTM
  deuteranopiaEnabled = false
  Reverts to DefaultTheme constants:
  ERROR_COLOR  = #FF0000 (red)
  PROMPT_COLOR = #00AA00 (green)
end note
deactivate CTM

AM -> SM : setSetting("DEUTERANOPIA_MODE", "false")
SM --> AM : ok

AM -> CW : repaint / reapply colours
CW --> AM : done
deactivate AM

note across
  Setting persists to heat.settings on next
  SettingsManager.saveSettings() call (Options > Apply).
  In-session toggle is immediate with no file I/O.
end note

@enduml
